com.software.reuze

Class dag_GraphNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.software.reuze.dag_GraphNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<Object>

    public class dag_GraphNode
extends Object
implements Comparable<Object>
    This class represents a node (vertex) that can be used with the Graph class.
    The node has a position in 3D space for 2D applications the z value should be zero.
    Each node should be given a unique ID number >= 0. Node ID numbers do not need to start at 0 (zero) or be sequential but they must be unique.
    It is the responsibility of the user to ensure that each node ID is unique as duplicate ID numbers can lead to unpredictable behavior.
    Author:
    Peter Lager
